        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 2:20PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 220 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Edgecomb, or near Surf City, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Topsail, Surf City, Woodside, and Edgecomb.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
